race.comment: IKASARA (3) is an interesting horse who resumes here. He only had one run last time in and failed but it was behind Autumn Glow in the Listed Darby Munro. His juvenile form was promising and if he's able to find it fresh he'll take catching. JUST LIKE GABY (8) was a smart winner fresh before a good effort in a stronger race here last time out when well backed. She sets up for every chance from the gate here. TARPAULIN (9) has been costly this time in but his past two runs have been good despite going under at $2 and $2.80. He's a backable price this time. LEGACY BAY (13) resumes. 1100m is on the shorter side for her but her 3yo form over the Winter reads well for this and she gets in light. SEA POEM (10) is racing very well and should be strong late.
